.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-diff 1  "diff " 
.SH NAME
diff \- Compare two images: report PSNR and the largest per\-channel difference
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdiff\fR [\fB\-\-min\-psnr\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIA\fR> <\fIB\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Compare two images: report PSNR and the largest per\-channel difference.
.PP
Both inputs are decoded to RGBA (a WebP, or any readable image), so a source and its WebP, or two WebP files, can be compared. With `\-\-min\-psnr`, exit 1 when the PSNR is below the threshold — the grep/diff convention, for CI gates.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-psnr\fR \fI<DB>\fR
Fail (exit 1) if the RGB PSNR is below this many decibels
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Print the comparison as JSON instead of text
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIA\fR>
The first image (a WebP, or any readable format)
.TP
<\fIB\fR>
The second image, compared against the first (same dimensions required)
